body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for reaching out to CarZoo customer support. My name is Jordan Bennett and I'm here to assist you. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Beverly. To better assist you, could you please provide me with your phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it's five five five, three two one, four five six seven.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you. And could you also provide me with your email address, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you for sharing that information, Beverly. Is there anything specific you need help with today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I'm feeling nervous about a recent return I made at one of your dealerships.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I understand, Beverly. Let's work together to resolve this. Thank you for bringing it to our attention. I will look into this matter further. Thank you for your time.

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Thank you, Jordan. I appreciate your assistance.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: You're welcome, Beverly. Have a great day! Goodbye.
